4 SYNOPSIS:
5 This bill would require the Department of Early
6 Childhood Education to develop guidelines for the
7 appropriate use of screen-based media in early
8 childhood education programs, which includes day care
9 centers, day care homes, group day care homes, night
10 care facilities, prekindergarten, and kindergarten.
11 This bill would require the Department of Early
12 Childhood Education, in collaboration with the State
13 Department of Human Resources (DHR) and the State
14 Department of Education, to develop screen time
15 standards for early childhood education programs.
16 This bill would require the standards to address
17 age-appropriate screen time limits, guidelines for what
18 constitutes high-quality programming, and best
19 practices for screen time in early childhood education
20 programs.
21 This bill would require the Department of Early
22 Childhood Education, in collaboration with DHR and the
23 State Board of Education, to create a training program
24 on the appropriate use of screen time for teachers and
25 other staff members who supervise children.
26 This bill would require day care centers, day
27 care homes, group day care homes, and night care
28 facilities to implement the guidelines and training
Page 1

facilities to implement the guidelines and training
29 requirements as a condition for licensure by DHR.
30 This bill would require certain prekindergarten
31 classrooms and each public kindergarten classroom to
32 implement the guidelines and training requirements.
33 This bill would require DHR to oversee the
34 implementation of this act for licensed child-care
35 facilities, the Secretary of the Department of Early
36 Childhood Education for prekindergarten classrooms, and
37 local boards of education for kindergarten classrooms.
38 This bill would also authorize the Department of
39 Early Childhood Education, DHR, and the State Board of
40 Education to adopt rules.
